1.00	Kaidan_(film)	Kwaidan (film)	Kwaidan Kaidan) is a 1964 Japanese portmanteau film directed by Masaki Kobayashi; the title means 'ghost story'. It is based on stories from Lafcadio Hearn's collections of Japanese folk tales. The film consists of four separate and unrelated stories. Kwaidan is the archaic transliteration of Kaidan, meaning "ghost story". It won the Special Jury Prize at the 1965 Cannes Film Festival, and received an Academy Award nomination for Best Foreign Language Film.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/ff/Kwaidanposterjapanese.jpg/220px-Kwaidanposterjapanese.jpg
